Established in 1980 and located in Ningbo, China, Shanshan Group is a corporative and multi-industry company, mainly engaging in the manufacturing and distribution of men’s garments and apparel with the brand name “Shanshan” or “FIRS,” and we also produce other series of clothes. As one of the most famous companies in China, Shanshan was listed in China’s Top 500 Key Enterprises, assessed by the State Council. We played and are still playing a leadership role in the garment industry of China. Shanshan, with our men&rsq...More
Established in 1980 and located in Ningbo, China, Shanshan Group is a corporative and multi-industry company, mainly engaging in the manufacturing and distribution of men’s garments and apparel with the brand name “Shanshan” or “FIRS,” and we also produce other series of clothes. As one of the most famous companies in China, Shanshan was listed in China’s Top 500 Key Enterprises, assessed by the State Council. We played and are still playing a leadership role in the garment industry of China. Shanshan, with our men’s classic suits under the brand name “FIRS,” is the first company in the garment industry of China to gain the Qualification of Environmental-friendly Products and the Certification of ISO9002 Quality System.

With our branding strategy “Multi-brands & Internationalization,” Shanshan Group has established a long-term and close relationship with many international apparel companies and is licensed to produce and distribute their well-known brands. With the goal to have 30 brands in 2010, Shanshan Group now owns 20 brands in different styles and at different market segments: 2 core brands - Shanshan (both men’s and ladies’ clothing) and Shanshan Sports; 10 original brands - such as FIRS, MGB, Firs & Design, Elteno, LaFancy, LeTuTu, Rosew, Bellson, etc; and 9 licensed or distributed brands such as Marco Azzali, Renoma Paris, Lubiam 1911, Le Coq Sportif, Callaway Golf Apparel, Pinky & Dianne, Munsingwear, Dunhill Sports, Smalto, Le Coq Sportif Golf Collection, QUA, etc. In total, the Group comprises 2 listed companies, 24 factories, 19 fashion apparel companies, and nearly 3000 franchising shops at home and abroad.Less





















